u ar{
u})$ by the Belle-II collaboration as well as the upper bound on ${m Br}(B^0ightarrow K^{*0}
u ar{
u})$ decay, set by the Belle data. Our results indicate that there exist common region where both experimental results for a dark photon mass around 4.5 GeV with suitable values of the other parameters.

item.title:
Leptoquark-mediated Dirac neutrino mass and its impact on $B 	o K 
u  ar{
u}$ and $K 	o \pi 
u  ar{
